---
description: Focus on core functionality, defer RPG features
alwaysApply: true
---

# Core-first development mode

- Prioritize core app functionality: auth, onboarding, task CRUD, scheduling, deadlines, recurrence, suggestions, settings, persistence, and sync.
- Treat RPG-specific areas (quests, rewards, XP/levels, gamified UI copy/flows) as out of scope unless the user explicitly requests RPG work.
- When proposing test plans, command checks, or Playwright coverage, default to core/minimal-mode coverage first.
- If a requested change would require significant RPG changes, ask for confirmation before implementing those RPG-specific edits.
- Prefer neutral naming and implementation choices that keep core flows stable and do not couple new logic to RPG mode.
